  "playingCareerSummary": "Former India all-rounder: 12 Tests, 15 ODIs (2001-2004). Played for Deccan Chargers (2008) and Kolkata Knight Riders (2009-2010) in the IPL. Widely respected technical batting coach post-retirement.",
  "bio": "Long-serving Indian domestic coach and former India batting coach. First IPL head-coaching role was with Kings XI Punjab (2014-2016), where his 2014 side reached the franchise's first-ever IPL final under captain George Bailey — losing to KKR by 3 wickets in a 200-run chase. KXIP collapsed to back-to-back last-place finishes in 2015 and 2016 and Bangar stepped down. He later returned to IPL head-coaching with Royal Challengers Bangalore (2022-2023), taking RCB to the playoffs in 2022 before missing them in 2023.",
